    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                        <date>Nov 16 1868</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I am much obliged for your note which gives so good an account of Mr Hardy’s management of the farm. I beg leave to acknowledge &amp; thank you for the sum of £259–11–10 due as rent &amp; placed to my account at the Union Bank—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                        <p>My dear Sir | Yours very faithfully Ch. R. Darwin <lb/> <lb/></p>
                        <p rend="left">J. Higgins Esq</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The payment was for CD’s farm at Beesby in Lincolnshire; Higgins was CD’s land agent. Higgins’s letter to CD has not been found. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2117.xml">Francis Hardy</ref> was CD’s tenant.</note>
                </div>
        
